	<tr>
		
			<td bgcolor="#DEDACB">
		
				<font face="verdana" size="2" color="black">
				After retrieving this component off of the *dead* DE magician at the gate in Najena(behind two Tentacle Terrors, four elementals, two Ogre Guards and 12 skeletons) I was informed that this item by itself is incomplete.  Apparently, you need a Cyclopean Toe, 144pp and one other component.  Also, these items (including the broom) must be brought to a particular NPC to create the new broom.  The new broom apparently allows the caster to greatly increase the stats on any Air Elemental pet upon casting.  You simply place the new broom in your melee slot and cast your Air Elemental Spell.  The new Air Elemental will supposedly sustain much more damage, has a much better AC and attacks for more damage than it would have if you had cast it without the broom.  <BR>
However, does anyone know what the 4th component is and who you bring the item to to create the focus object?<BR>
<BR>
Kulgan of Crydee (Brell Server)
				</font>
